<DocsLayout title="Project Onboarding" description="How to onboard new developers and AI agents using Engrams CLI.">
  <h1>Project Onboarding & Agent Orientation</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    When a new developer joins your team or you start a fresh conversation with an AI agent, they need a quick way to get oriented. Engrams provides a structured onboarding flow using product context, active sprint goals, and recent activity.
  </p>

  <h2>Orienting an AI Agent Instantly</h2>
  <p>
    Instead of spending time copy-pasting code trees or drafting custom explanations, your AI agent can run a standard series of orientation commands at startup:
  </p>

  <div class="steps">
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Read the Product Context:</strong>
        <p>The agent runs <code>engrams product-context get</code> to understand the project's purpose, tech stack, and primary architecture goals.</p>
        <pre><code>engrams product-context get</code></pre>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Read the Active Context:</strong>
        <p>The agent runs <code>engrams active-context get</code> to see what the team is currently working on, what open questions exist, and what the immediate next steps are.</p>
        <pre><code>engrams active-context get</code></pre>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Fetch Recent Activity:</strong>
        <p>The agent runs <code>engrams activity</code> to get a reverse-chronological digest of recent additions and updates, showing what code decisions and patterns were logged recently.</p>
        <pre><code>engrams activity --hours 48</code></pre>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <h2>Example Onboarding Session</h2>
  <p>
    Here is what a typical agent startup sequence looks like under the hood:
  </p>
  <pre><code>{`AI: [Running: engrams product-context get]
    Result: { "stack": "Rust, SQLite", "purpose": "High-performance CLI tool" }

AI: [Running: engrams active-context get]
    Result: { "focus": "Implementing link commands", "status": "InProgress" }

AI: [Running: engrams activity --hours 24]
    Result: [
      { "type": "decision", "summary": "Use rusqlite with bundled feature", "timestamp": "2026-07-10T12:00:00Z" }
    ]

AI: "Hello! I see this is a Rust CLI tool utilizing SQLite (via rusqlite with bundled features).
    The current active focus is implementing the 'link' commands. I am ready to assist."`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Summary of Onboarding Commands</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>engrams product-context get</code> — Retrieves the stable high-level overview.</li>
    <li><code>engrams active-context get</code> — Retrieves the current session focus and status.</li>
    <li><code>engrams activity [--hours &lt;N&gt;]</code> — Generates a chronological digest of recent changes across all memory records.</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>

